Debian 8.8, Ubuntu 16.04.2 LTS and CentOS 7  do not need patching to compile anymore


CentOS 7:
using yum, install: csh gcc gcc-c++ gcc-gfortran java-1.7.0-openjdk-devel python-devel ant gtk2-devel libjpeg-turbo-devel libtool ImageMagick libXt-devel xterm mesa-libGLU-devel kernel-devel perl-Digest-Perl-MD5 perl-Digest-MD5 bzip2 perl-Env 

Debian 8.8:
using apt-get, install: bzip2 build-essential autoconf libtool ant pkg-config gtk+-2.0-dev libxt-dev csh gfortran openjdk-7-jdk python-dev libjpeg-dev imagemagick xterm libfreetype6-dev libfl-dev libtool-bin

Ubuntu 16.04.2 LTS:
using apt-get, install: bzip2 build-essential autoconf libtool ant pkg-config gtk+-2.0-dev libxt-dev csh gfortran openjdk-8-jdk python-dev libjpeg-dev imagemagick xterm libfreetype6-dev libfl-dev libtool-bin

All Distros:
following installation of packages as outlined above, go to directory ecce-v7.0, and do
sh build.sh

Make sure to answer 'y' when asked if you want to skip checks next time, or you get stuck in a loop.

Successful build will generate an executable .csh file called install_ecce.v7.0.csh
